WEBVTT

00:01.100 --> 00:02.624
Previously on Elementary...

00:02.670 --> 00:04.160
How much heroin
is that?
Oh, that's enough.

00:07.140 --> 00:11.133
Wow.
Please make
yourself at home.

00:11.170 --> 00:13.070
We want you to be as
comfortable here at Leda

00:13.110 --> 00:14.099
as you were at
your old job.

00:16.350 --> 00:17.374
We found your
nutmeg concoction.

00:17.410 --> 00:18.377
What are you talking about?

00:18.410 --> 00:20.219
You dissolve
corpses for money.

00:20.250 --> 00:23.219
GREGSON: Her name is
Melanie Vilkas, 24 years old.

00:23.250 --> 00:24.478
She went missing a few days ago.

00:24.520 --> 00:26.385
And the reason I couldn't
bring Kitty with me?

00:26.420 --> 00:28.285
GREGSON:
Take a look at her back.

00:28.320 --> 00:31.323
They're the same markings
that are on Kitty's back.

00:31.360 --> 00:33.328
This is why I became
a detective--

00:33.360 --> 00:35.157
to hunt this man.
I'm ready.

00:35.200 --> 00:36.394
HOLMES:
Simon de Merville.

00:36.430 --> 00:37.829
Lengthy record.

00:37.870 --> 00:40.566
He's not the man
who raped me.
What?

00:40.600 --> 00:43.330
I'm watching the news-- the man
you were looking for was killed.

00:43.370 --> 00:45.235
Yeah, at least it's over.

00:45.270 --> 00:46.476
Who was that?

00:46.510 --> 00:48.637
My boss at Leda,
Del Gruner. Why?

00:48.680 --> 00:52.116
DEL: And insurance is
a $4 trillion industry.

00:52.150 --> 00:53.139
KI'I'I'Y:
I was wrong, Watson.

00:53.180 --> 00:55.671
De Merville didn't hurt me.

00:55.720 --> 00:57.312
He did.

01:04.160 --> 01:06.299
MAN: Ms. Winter, to what
do I owe the pleasure?

01:06.330 --> 01:11.120
Uh, it's-it's been almost a week
since I sent you my report.

01:11.170 --> 01:12.762
Ijust... I wanted to
know your thoughts.

01:12.800 --> 01:15.337
Not much we don't
already know, hmm?

01:15.370 --> 01:19.579
Latif Malak was taken
on his way home from school

01:19.610 --> 01:21.305
six months ago.

01:21.340 --> 01:23.308
His parents received
a ransom note.

01:23.350 --> 01:25.272
We left it where
the kidnappers asked,

01:25.310 --> 01:27.278
only they never collected it.

01:27.320 --> 01:29.311
And Latif was
never returned.

01:31.320 --> 01:34.255
What did you think of the
bit about the backpack?

01:40.800 --> 01:42.358
This is Latif's backpack,

01:42.400 --> 01:44.129
the one that you found
in the allewNay

01:44.170 --> 01:46.297
that he would cut through on
his way home from school, right?

01:46.340 --> 01:47.693
Where did
you get that?

01:47.740 --> 01:50.607
Only, look at this-- the
chest clasp is closed.

01:50.640 --> 01:53.279
You thought that the bag came
loose during a struggle,

01:53.310 --> 01:55.278
but I defy you
to shake it off anyone

01:55.310 --> 01:57.278
when that clasp is locked.

02:00.420 --> 02:01.910
Someone took Latif
and his backpack,

02:01.950 --> 02:03.508
then once he was stashed,

02:03.550 --> 02:05.780
they came back and they planted
the bag in the allewNay.

02:05.820 --> 02:07.253
Which would mean
that the abduction

02:07.290 --> 02:08.587
happened somewhere else.

02:08.620 --> 02:10.258
Which means that you
haven't actually examined

02:10.290 --> 02:11.154
the real crime scene.

02:11.190 --> 02:13.226
Let's just cut to the chase,
shall we?

02:13.260 --> 02:15.899
You want me to talk
to John Hodge again.

02:15.930 --> 02:17.591
He is a registered sex offender

02:17.630 --> 02:19.769
whose flat Latif would walk by
every single day.

02:19.800 --> 02:22.803
You think that the kidnapper
killed Latif by accident--

02:22.840 --> 02:24.808
that's why he never came back
to retrieve his ransom.

02:24.840 --> 02:27.377
But I think it's because he
already had what he wanted--

02:27.410 --> 02:29.241
Latif.

02:29.280 --> 02:31.339
You're a very pretty
girl, Ms. Winter.

02:31.380 --> 02:33.439
But you're
not police.

02:33.480 --> 02:37.587
You mind your business,
and we'll mind ours, all right?

02:51.770 --> 02:53.761
Problem?

02:54.800 --> 02:56.529
You're just
in my way.

02:58.610 --> 03:00.601
Thank you.

03:07.580 --> 03:09.844
(footsteps approaching)

03:09.890 --> 03:11.846
She's asleep finally.

03:11.890 --> 03:13.414
I'm worried.

03:13.460 --> 03:15.451
These last few days
were a lot.

03:15.490 --> 03:16.980
I think she needs more help
than we can give her.

03:17.030 --> 03:20.227
You think she's wrong
about your employer, Gruner.

03:20.260 --> 03:21.818
Of course she's wrong.

03:21.860 --> 03:24.397
I reached out
to the Osweiler family

03:24.430 --> 03:26.432
shortly after you arrived.

03:27.370 --> 03:28.928
As it turns out,

03:28.970 --> 03:30.938
they did change their
insurance company last year.

03:30.970 --> 03:33.530
Their names should have been
on the list he gave you.

03:33.580 --> 03:35.775
Wait a second,
are you seriously...?

03:35.810 --> 03:37.471
Knowing their address
would have allowed us

03:37.510 --> 03:38.772
to find Simon de Merville
much sooner.

03:38.810 --> 03:41.517
Perhaps even
before he was killed.

03:41.550 --> 03:43.415
You're upset, and so is Kitty,

03:43.450 --> 03:45.281
but if you think
that my new boss

03:45.320 --> 03:46.878
just happens to be the same guy

03:46.920 --> 03:48.717
who took her in London, I...

03:48.760 --> 03:50.728
I am simply raising
the possibility

03:50.760 --> 03:52.352
that nothing
about your relationship

03:52.400 --> 03:54.356
with Gruner "just happened."

03:54.400 --> 03:56.618
That you were targeted.

03:56.670 --> 03:58.797
During your
courtship with Leda,

03:58.830 --> 04:00.639
there were multiple interviews,

04:00.670 --> 04:02.501
multiple background checks,
were there not?

04:03.810 --> 04:06.335
Would have been a very useful
way to gather intelligence.

04:06.380 --> 04:07.404
On what?

04:07.440 --> 04:10.045
Kitty. Me. You.

04:10.080 --> 04:11.945
Imagine you're him.

04:11.980 --> 04:15.347
Five years ago, you took
and tortured an innocent girl.

04:15.380 --> 04:17.348
She escaped.

04:17.390 --> 04:19.358
You don't know
how much she knows

04:19.390 --> 04:21.358
or what she was able
to tell the police.

04:21.390 --> 04:24.882
The only thing that you know
is that you were never caught.

04:24.930 --> 04:26.898
Now, luclq for you,
you're very wealthy.

04:26.930 --> 04:28.488
You can look for her.

04:28.530 --> 04:30.327
You can keep tabs.

04:30.370 --> 04:32.338
What might you think
when you realize

04:32.370 --> 04:34.668
she has taken up
with a renowned detective?

04:34.700 --> 04:36.463
Oh, so this is all about you.

04:36.510 --> 04:39.331
Us.

04:39.380 --> 04:41.530
He realized we were
educating her, shaping her.

04:41.580 --> 04:43.343
How long might it be

04:43.380 --> 04:45.575
before we turned _
our collective attention to him?

04:46.880 --> 04:48.848
Now, there's
strength in numbers.

04:48.880 --> 04:51.849
Killing one of us might
incite the other two.

04:51.890 --> 04:55.849
But giving us an answer
he believed that we sought,

04:55.890 --> 04:57.687
giving us a culprit...

04:57.730 --> 04:59.994
Del framed De Merville?

05:00.030 --> 05:04.069
We don't know why De Merville's
partner attacked him.

05:04.100 --> 05:06.466
Perhaps he was paid to do it.

05:06.500 --> 05:08.468
What if he left
the phone at the bar

05:08.500 --> 05:10.434
that Melanie Vilkas
disappeared from?

05:10.470 --> 05:11.801
She was killed
to make it look

05:11.840 --> 05:13.569
like Kitty's attacker
was in New York.

05:13.610 --> 05:16.738
De Merville would have been
killed to put the matter to bed.

05:16.780 --> 05:20.614
So how, in this scenario,
does Del know the partner?

05:20.650 --> 05:23.016
"In this scenario,"
he's a man of means

05:23.050 --> 05:25.439
and a pervert
of the highest order.

05:25.490 --> 05:26.855
Is it really so hard to imagine

05:26.890 --> 05:28.619
he made friends
with a sex trafficker?

05:28.660 --> 05:30.389
Say you're right.

05:30.430 --> 05:32.022
Say the Osweilers' names did
pop up on the list

05:32.060 --> 05:33.527
that he got from the IRB.

05:33.560 --> 05:35.448
He would have only
taken them off if he knew

05:35.500 --> 05:37.923
the police were looking for
De Merville in Gerritsen Beach.

05:37.970 --> 05:39.699
He needed time to get
to the Osweiler residence

05:39.740 --> 05:41.537
to murder the man himself.

05:41.570 --> 05:43.538
WATSON: We only knew Gerritsen
Beach was significant

05:43.570 --> 05:46.107
because we traced the call that
De Merville made to his sister.

05:46.140 --> 05:47.698
I never told Del about that.

05:47.740 --> 05:49.708
You ever let anyone
at Leda handle your phone?

05:49.750 --> 05:52.719
No.

05:52.750 --> 05:55.810
They gave me
a company phone, though.

05:55.850 --> 05:58.080
(cell phone rings)

06:02.990 --> 06:04.958
Hello.

06:04.990 --> 06:06.821
Joan, it's Del.

06:07.830 --> 06:09.798
I'm gonna have to let you go.

06:09.830 --> 06:11.468
Too much has gone on this week.

06:11.500 --> 06:13.092
It's too bad, really.

06:13.140 --> 06:14.459
For a while there, you were

06:14.500 --> 06:16.502
a great help.

06:31.690 --> 06:33.658
GREGSON:
Del Gruner?

06:33.690 --> 06:35.658
Captain Gregson.

06:35.690 --> 06:37.453
We'd like to ask you
some questions.

06:39.730 --> 06:41.027
No, I'm sorry.

06:41.060 --> 06:42.493
I've never seen
this man before.

06:42.530 --> 06:43.861
His name was
Ervin Bogdani.

06:43.900 --> 06:47.461
He was a sex trafficker
for the Albanian mafia.

06:47.500 --> 06:50.708
He made an attempt on the life
of this man a few days ago.

06:50.740 --> 06:52.708
Recognize him?

06:52.740 --> 06:55.208
I think I do-- he was
in the news this week, right?

06:55.240 --> 06:58.038
He, um, he killed a girl,
left her on a pier.

06:58.080 --> 07:00.674
Captain, are you approaching
anything resembling a point?

07:00.720 --> 07:02.779
GREGSON: Your client is a person
of interest in the murder

07:02.820 --> 07:05.186
of the person he
just mentioned--

07:05.220 --> 07:06.187
Melanie Vilkas.

07:06.220 --> 07:08.586
I watch the news, too.

07:08.620 --> 07:10.588
This is the man
who killed her.

07:10.630 --> 07:13.224
Actually, we're not
so sure about that.

07:13.260 --> 07:15.228
Can we cut to the chase?

07:15.260 --> 07:17.865
The two of you are close
with Joan Watson.

07:17.900 --> 07:19.663
Mr. Gruner fired her
last night.

07:19.700 --> 07:21.839
Now he's a suspect
in a murder case

07:21.870 --> 07:23.167
that's already
been solved.
It's okay, Jim.

07:23.210 --> 07:25.007
I don't mind answering
a few questions.

07:25.040 --> 07:27.008
It's our understanding
that you spent some time

07:27.040 --> 07:28.598
in London five years ago.

07:28.640 --> 07:30.039
We'd acquired a British company.

07:30.080 --> 07:31.672
I was there
for about six months.

07:31.710 --> 07:34.679
During those six months,
another girl was taken.

07:34.720 --> 07:38.508
She was raped, beaten, branded,
just like Melanie.

07:38.550 --> 07:40.586
Only, this girl escaped.

07:40.620 --> 07:42.759
GREGSON: She thought she broke a
few of her attacker's fingers

07:42.790 --> 07:44.519
before she got away.

07:44.560 --> 07:46.926
You broke your right ring
and middle fingers.

07:46.960 --> 07:48.848
I can tell.

07:48.900 --> 07:50.094
They didn't heal right.

07:50.130 --> 07:52.098
Yeah, remember when boxing
was the new jogging?

07:52.130 --> 07:55.167
Well, I, uh, I took on
a heavy bag and lost.

07:55.200 --> 07:57.805
I'm sorry,
but 1-1 have to ask.

07:57.840 --> 08:01.037
I-Is this other girl
named Kitty?

08:01.080 --> 08:03.674
Joan mentioned
her a few times.

08:03.710 --> 08:04.904
Uh... I know

08:04.950 --> 08:06.178
she_su_rvived an attack
Similar to the one

08:06.210 --> 08:06.972
that you're describing.

08:07.020 --> 08:09.614
We're not at liberty
to discuss that.

08:09.650 --> 08:11.242
We're clone here.
Jim...

08:11.290 --> 08:14.259
I'm sorry if your consultant
had her feelings hurt.

08:14.290 --> 08:17.259
But Mr. Gruner is the face
of Leda Insurance.

08:17.290 --> 08:18.985
He works with several
prominent charities.

08:19.030 --> 08:20.998
He's given millions of dollars
and hundreds of hours

08:21.030 --> 08:23.191
of his time, and he was
also a major contributor

08:23.230 --> 08:25.266
to the mayor's last
election campaign.

08:25.300 --> 08:26.858
So unless you want
to explain to Hizzoner

08:26.900 --> 08:28.936
why Del Gruner is suing
the New York Police Department,

08:28.970 --> 08:30.938
I suggest you let
this matter drop.

08:30.970 --> 08:32.733
Gentlemen.

08:37.780 --> 08:39.577
It was all over
his face.

08:41.180 --> 08:42.738
GREGSON:
I know.

08:42.790 --> 08:44.746
BELL: Guy's got us
right where he wants us.

08:44.790 --> 08:47.759
Firing you makes this all
look retaliatory.

08:47.790 --> 08:49.758
Kitty never saw his face,

08:49.790 --> 08:52.281
and her rape kit in London
didn't turn up any viable DNA.

08:52.330 --> 08:54.150
And all the evidence
here in New York points

08:54.200 --> 08:55.599
to Simon de Merville.

08:55.630 --> 08:56.995
I'm not gonna
make it easy

08:57.030 --> 08:58.588
for him to sue
the department.

08:58.630 --> 08:59.995
I'll take a leave
of absence.

09:00.040 --> 09:01.029
Screw that.

09:01.070 --> 09:02.935
We do this, we do it together.

09:02.970 --> 09:04.005
(elevator bell dings)

09:09.850 --> 09:12.842
MAN: This is a 55-year-old male
with weight gain and edema

09:12.880 --> 09:14.768
as well as a history
of hypothyroidism.

09:14.820 --> 09:16.788
(knocking on door)

09:16.820 --> 09:18.617
HOLMES: Kitty Winter?
Hypothyroidism is secondary

09:18.650 --> 09:21.050
to radioactive iodine
for Graves disease many years...

09:21.090 --> 09:22.785
My name's
Sherlock Holmes.

09:22.830 --> 09:24.786
We met yesterday
after a fashion.

09:24.830 --> 09:26.058
You were blocking my
way at Scotland Yard.

09:26.090 --> 09:27.250
I've brought
your tablet back.

09:28.960 --> 09:30.268
How did you get this address?

09:30.300 --> 09:32.063
DCI Hopkins.

09:32.100 --> 09:34.933
He oversees the inspector
you've been harassing-- Davies.

09:34.970 --> 09:37.859
I haven't been harassing anyone.
Yes, you have.

09:37.910 --> 09:39.969
But with good reason--
Davies is a good man,

09:40.010 --> 09:42.171
but he's a limited thinker
and he requires harassment.

09:43.680 --> 09:45.648
Are you a policeman?

09:45.680 --> 09:48.012
No, certainly not.
I'm a consultant.

09:48.050 --> 09:49.847
I'm currently in the employ
of another department,

09:49.890 --> 09:53.155
but I make myself available
to the police when needed.

09:53.190 --> 09:56.626
You make your wage as
a transcriptionist, do you not?

09:56.660 --> 09:59.788
Sounds like
lonely work.

09:59.830 --> 10:02.867
Anyway, I read your report,
and I think you're right.

10:02.900 --> 10:04.265
Latif Malak was not taken
from that alleyway,

10:04.300 --> 10:05.699
he was taken
from somewhere else.

10:05.730 --> 10:06.936
I would very much like
to discuss

10:06.970 --> 10:08.267
the subject with you further,

10:08.300 --> 10:11.303
but preferably not
through a door.

10:11.340 --> 10:13.808
You can keep your knife
pointed at me if you like.

10:13.840 --> 10:15.808
How, how did you...
My sense

10:15.840 --> 10:18.741
from inquiring about you is
that I'm your last and best hope

10:18.780 --> 10:22.887
of finding Latif and bringing
his abductor to justice.

10:25.020 --> 10:26.908
Do you wish my help or not?

10:30.160 --> 10:32.151
(door unlocking)

10:50.250 --> 10:53.139
How are you feeling?

10:53.180 --> 10:54.977
Better. Thank you.

10:55.020 --> 10:56.044
I've eaten already.

10:56.080 --> 10:57.718
These are for you.

10:57.750 --> 10:59.388
I'm not really hungry.

10:59.420 --> 11:01.957
These are for you.

11:01.990 --> 11:03.924
Where's Watson?

11:03.960 --> 11:05.928
She's assisting Captain Gregson
and Detective Bell

11:05.960 --> 11:09.691
with a more thorough
investigation of Del Gruner.

11:09.730 --> 11:12.096
Did you know that "Del" is
short for "Adelbert"?

11:13.500 --> 11:15.365
Small wonder
the man is a sadist.

11:18.110 --> 11:20.078
Shouldn't you be with her?

11:20.110 --> 11:22.135
My place is here with you.

11:22.180 --> 11:24.068
Sherlock...

11:24.110 --> 11:25.998
I'm ashamed of myself.
I allowed you to leave

11:26.050 --> 11:27.119
the morgue
unaccompanied yesterday.

11:27.150 --> 11:28.708
You thought the man who hurt you

11:28.750 --> 11:30.308
was still at large,
and I thought...

11:30.350 --> 11:32.045
(low grunt)

11:32.090 --> 11:34.183
I should've been there.

11:34.220 --> 11:36.279
When you realized who he was.

11:38.030 --> 11:40.328
I'm leaving.

11:40.360 --> 11:42.055
(sniffs)

11:44.330 --> 11:47.163
A few days ago...

11:47.200 --> 11:50.067
you recommended
that I go back to London,

11:50.110 --> 11:51.998
and I should've listened to you.

11:54.010 --> 11:56.899
I wasn't ready
for this, Sherlock.

11:56.950 --> 11:59.168
It's all been
worked out with my mum.

11:59.210 --> 12:00.370
There's a ticket for me at JFK.

12:00.420 --> 12:02.240
I leave at noon.

12:06.120 --> 12:08.088
Ijust...

12:08.120 --> 12:11.021
wanted you to know
that I'm sorry.

12:12.560 --> 12:15.950
For going after
De Merville's sister.

12:16.000 --> 12:17.888
The captain was
right to sack me.

12:17.930 --> 12:20.160
You've been suspended.
There is a difference.

12:22.140 --> 12:24.904
I know now that I can't...

12:24.940 --> 12:27.807
help you.

12:27.840 --> 12:30.047
I'll just distract.

12:31.810 --> 12:33.846
I'll arrange for the police

12:33.880 --> 12:36.940
to take you to the airport.

12:45.590 --> 12:47.148
WATSON:
Hello?

12:47.200 --> 12:49.156
So, it took a lot of visits

12:49.200 --> 12:51.259
to a lot of unsavory places,

12:51.300 --> 12:53.063
but Marcus and I were able
to confirm that no one

12:53.100 --> 12:55.489
from the Albanian mob ordered
a hit on Simon de Merville.

12:55.540 --> 12:56.837
This lends credence

12:56.870 --> 12:58.303
to the idea that Ervin Bogdani

12:58.340 --> 13:00.399
was taking orders
from someone else

13:00.440 --> 13:01.839
when he came at De Merville
with a knife

13:01.880 --> 13:03.177
the other day.
Only there's

13:03.210 --> 13:05.178
no proof to connect
Bogdani to Del.

13:05.210 --> 13:06.370
Stop calling him that, please.

13:06.410 --> 13:08.344
Del?
Del. Del is the man

13:08.380 --> 13:10.041
who hired you.
A friendly face, a facade.

13:10.090 --> 13:12.012
We seek Gruner!

13:12.050 --> 13:14.154
So, what's all this?

13:14.190 --> 13:16.078
Patrons from_ the bar that
Melanie Vilkas disappeared from

13:16.120 --> 13:19.897
recalled seeing Ervin Bogdani
the night of the crime.

13:19.930 --> 13:22.023
He is in all likelihood
the man who took her.

13:22.060 --> 13:24.494
Her murder, on the
other hand, was the work

13:24.530 --> 13:27.135
of the same man
who took Kitty-- Gruner.

13:27.170 --> 13:29.388
Take a look
at the autopsy report.

13:29.440 --> 13:31.499
He revels in his work
and who he is.

13:31.540 --> 13:34.031
I think it's highly unlikely
that he limited himself

13:34.080 --> 13:37.572
to just Kitty and Melanie Vilkas
over the last five years.

13:37.610 --> 13:40.340
But you and Kitty were never
able to identify other victims.

13:40.380 --> 13:43.110
Women with brands
on their backs.

13:43.150 --> 13:45.141
Gruner is a habitual murderer,
it stands to reason

13:45.190 --> 13:47.385
he is also practiced in the art
of disposing of bodies.

13:47.420 --> 13:49.149
He may be so practiced

13:49.190 --> 13:51.226
that no other victims
have ever turned up.

13:51.260 --> 13:53.148
Or they have,
but his various signatures

13:53.200 --> 13:55.054
were deliberately destroyed.

13:55.100 --> 13:56.897
Well, Melanie Vilkas' body
turned up.

13:56.930 --> 13:58.420
He wanted us to find her.

13:58.470 --> 14:01.394
We must identify the victims
he did not wish us to find.

14:01.440 --> 14:04.159
Within these boxes
lie open cases.

14:04.210 --> 14:06.633
Women who were taken and/or
murdered in the New York area

14:06.670 --> 14:09.138
over the last ten years.

14:09.180 --> 14:10.977
Their abductors and
their killers were

14:11.010 --> 14:12.307
never identified.
I will wager at least

14:12.350 --> 14:14.147
some of them
fell victim to Gruner.

14:14.180 --> 14:16.444
If we can cobble together
even a theoretical victim pool,

14:16.480 --> 14:19.210
we may find evidence,
which will undo him.

14:19.250 --> 14:21.616
In other words, we're looking
for a needle in a haystack.

14:21.660 --> 14:24.584
Needles. But yes,
our night will be long.

14:25.660 --> 14:28.128
(sighs)

14:36.100 --> 14:39.137
Did Kitty get to the
airport all right?

14:39.170 --> 14:42.947
She should be arriving
in London shortly.

14:47.320 --> 14:49.311
I wanted to apologize.

14:51.250 --> 14:53.354
You were right about everything.

14:53.390 --> 14:56.518
He lied to me.

14:56.560 --> 15:00.189
It's my fault that
Kitty had to leave.

15:00.230 --> 15:03.267
You were manipulated
by a brilliant psychopath

15:03.300 --> 15:07.066
for whom lying is as autonomic
a process as breathing.

15:08.500 --> 15:10.229
Join the club.

15:10.270 --> 15:12.067
(cell phone dings)

15:13.310 --> 15:15.107
It's Kitty.

15:15.140 --> 15:17.540
She just landed.

15:45.240 --> 15:47.674
