15:59.750 --> 16:01.513
(gasps)

16:01.560 --> 16:04.586
(groans)

16:04.630 --> 16:07.098
Well, looks like
you made some progress.

16:07.130 --> 16:08.427
After you fell asleep,

16:08.460 --> 16:09.757
I continued going
through the files.

16:09.800 --> 16:10.994
These are the women

16:11.030 --> 16:12.622
who fell into the widest net.

16:12.670 --> 16:14.137
Women who match Kitty's

16:14.170 --> 16:16.195
and Melanie Vilkas'
general appearance

16:16.240 --> 16:19.334
and age, but whose remains
were either never found or

16:19.370 --> 16:21.179
found in such condition
as to potentially obscure

16:21.210 --> 16:23.576
the scarring
from Gruner's brand.

16:23.610 --> 16:26.408
From there, I looked
at the details of each case.

16:26.450 --> 16:28.042
In some, the abductions
did not match

16:28.080 --> 16:29.775
what we believe
to be Gruner's M.O.

16:29.820 --> 16:32.141
The drugging
and stealing away of women.

16:32.190 --> 16:34.010
Others occurred at times
that we can confirm

16:34.060 --> 16:36.119
he was out of the country.

16:36.160 --> 16:38.048
In this way, I've managed
to narrow our search

16:38.090 --> 16:41.594
down to... _
three potential candidates.

16:41.630 --> 16:44.167
Okay, well, like you said last
night, this is all theoretical.

16:44.200 --> 16:46.191
You're basing this all
on Kitty and Melanie Vilkas.

16:46.230 --> 16:48.664
And considering Gruner left
Melanie's body for us to find,

16:48.700 --> 16:52.101
I mean, she could be as false
a lead as Simon de Merville.

16:52.140 --> 16:54.176
It's unlikely the rest
of what Gruner did

16:54.210 --> 16:56.371
to Melanie Vilkas was faked.

16:56.410 --> 16:58.469
A deranged person can
no more choose

16:58.510 --> 17:00.614
their sexual proclivities
than a healthy one.

17:00.650 --> 17:02.447
I'm hoping he made
some strategic error.

17:02.480 --> 17:05.244
Giving away more information
than he intended.

17:05.290 --> 17:07.679
Oh.

17:07.720 --> 17:09.449
What about her? Francine Bianco?
She kind of looks like his type.

17:09.490 --> 17:11.219
And whoever killed
her burned her body.

17:11.260 --> 17:13.558
It could've been Gruner trying
to hide the brand marks.

17:13.600 --> 17:15.227
Why didn't she make the list?

17:15.260 --> 17:16.454
Ms. Bianco was held
by her captor

17:16.500 --> 17:18.058
for almost one year.

17:18.100 --> 17:19.192
Neither Melanie Vilkas

17:19.230 --> 17:20.697
nor any of our three
suspected matches

17:20.740 --> 17:22.139
were held for more
than a month.

17:22.170 --> 17:24.263
Was that really enough
to discount her?

17:24.310 --> 17:25.607
I'm sorry, did you
come up with a better

17:25.640 --> 17:27.107
process of elimination
in your sleep?

17:27.140 --> 17:28.232
You told me to take a break.

17:28.280 --> 17:30.145
These are our strongest leads.

17:30.180 --> 17:31.647
Might Francine Bianco
join their number eventually?

17:31.680 --> 17:33.409
Yes, of course she might.

17:33.450 --> 17:35.213
Gruner might have killed all of
these women or he might have

17:35.250 --> 17:38.139
killed none of them.
I have to start somewhere.

17:38.190 --> 17:41.785
(phone rings)

17:41.820 --> 17:44.220
Detective, you have
myself and Watson.

17:44.260 --> 17:46.148
BELL: _
Hey, I've been turning over
rocks in Gruner's life

17:46.190 --> 17:49.091
and a name jumped out
at me: Tabitha Laird.

17:49.130 --> 17:51.098
Is that someone you
think he killed?

17:51.130 --> 17:53.166
I think it's somebody
he may have wanted to kill.

17:53.200 --> 17:54.599
Tabitha Laird is alive.

17:54.640 --> 17:57.404
I'm on my way
to talk to her right now.

17:57.440 --> 18:00.409
I'm sorry.
Just give me a second, okay?

18:00.440 --> 18:02.635
Hey, hon?

18:02.680 --> 18:05.274
You color Mommy
something nice, okay?

18:12.450 --> 18:14.554
I think there
must be some confusion.

18:14.590 --> 18:17.184
_ I never filed _
a police complaint against Del.

18:17.230 --> 18:19.255
No, Ms. Laird, we know that.
But you work for a charity

18:19.290 --> 18:21.224
for foster kids, right?

18:21.260 --> 18:22.488
Hearth and Home
Foundaﬂon?
