testing me like this?

23:59.700 --> 24:00.997
You should be careful, Del.

24:01.040 --> 24:02.667
We're not in some basement.

24:02.700 --> 24:04.759
I don't have duct tape
around my eyes and wrists.

24:04.810 --> 24:06.562
Let go.

24:06.610 --> 24:07.872
Or we'll find
out how you do

24:07.910 --> 24:10.674
against a woman who can
actually fight back.

24:23.530 --> 24:24.519
WATSON:
I did a 12-week psych rotation,

24:24.560 --> 24:25.720
and I still couldn't tell you

24:25.760 --> 24:27.057
how someone could stand
in the middle

24:27.090 --> 24:28.489
of a charity benefit,
be accused of

24:28.530 --> 24:29.519
a string of murders
and tell jokes.

24:29.560 --> 24:30.697
I'm just as
baffled by you.

24:30.730 --> 24:31.992
You just gave
our adversary

24:32.030 --> 24:33.736
the names we were able
to diVine.

24:33.770 --> 24:35.829
If those women
were indeed his victims,

24:35.870 --> 24:37.838
now he knows our plan.
He can interfere.

24:37.870 --> 24:40.134
We are playing a guessing game.
You know that as well as I do.

24:40.170 --> 24:42.638
I do not guess!
You know what I mean.

24:42.680 --> 24:44.500
Having these women's pictures,
the dates and times

24:44.550 --> 24:46.575
they disappeared-- it's not
the same as physical evidence.

24:46.610 --> 24:48.874
We don't have bodies to autopsy,
crime scenes to visit.

24:48.920 --> 24:50.979
It is a poor detective
who blames her evidence, Watson.

24:51.020 --> 24:52.214
I wanted to see his face.

24:52.250 --> 24:53.683
I wanted to say
those three names

24:53.720 --> 24:55.051
and see what he did.

24:55.090 --> 24:57.524
And?

24:57.560 --> 24:59.152
Nothing.

24:59.190 --> 25:01.556
Yeah, well, that doesn't
mean we're not right.

25:01.600 --> 25:03.727
I did not come here
to scrap the list, okay?

25:03.770 --> 25:05.829
I came here because
I think it is incomplete.

25:05.870 --> 25:08.839
There was one name that did
get a rise out of Gruner.

25:08.870 --> 25:10.633
Tabitha Laird.
She was there tonight.

25:10.670 --> 25:12.228
When he realized
we'd been to see her,

25:12.270 --> 25:13.669
he lost it.

25:13.710 --> 25:15.132
Define "lost it."

25:18.310 --> 25:21.040
I saw him tonight--
the real him.

25:22.720 --> 25:24.608
Tabitha Laird may not fall
into the victim profile

25:24.650 --> 25:26.641
that we cobbled together,
but I am telling you,

25:26.690 --> 25:28.681
he's got plans for her.

25:30.160 --> 25:31.821
Tabitha Laird could not
be more dissimilar

25:31.860 --> 25:34.727
to the three women we
were able to isolate.

25:36.330 --> 25:38.821
Perhaps his interest in her
is genuinely romantic.

25:38.870 --> 25:40.735
There have been serial killers
with wives, girlfriends.

25:40.770 --> 25:42.635
These men are outliers,
but they do exist.

25:42.670 --> 25:44.308
No, we know what Gruner
does to women.

25:44.340 --> 25:46.604
We know what he sees
when he looks at them.

25:46.640 --> 25:48.801
This thing with Tabitha, it's...

25:48.840 --> 25:51.001
I can't explain it,
but there was something there.

25:51.050 --> 25:53.268
Then the only thing
that we know for certain

25:53.310 --> 25:57.019
is that I've wasted a great deal
of time on victimology.

26:00.320 --> 26:02.709
We're going to get Kitty back.

26:04.660 --> 26:06.855
We're going to
take care of this.

26:06.890 --> 26:09.757
She'll come back, and you'll get
to finish what you started.

26:12.800 --> 26:14.597
You should call the captain,

26:14.640 --> 26:16.369
arrange for protective detail
for Tabitha Laird

26:16.400 --> 26:17.731
and her son.

26:17.770 --> 26:19.931
I will revisit
every file in every box.

26:19.970 --> 26:21.631
If she is in
play for Gruner,

26:21.680 --> 26:23.773
then we will need to
broaden our parameters.

26:23.810 --> 26:26.745
We will need women in their 40s,
taller women, women with...

26:29.780 --> 26:30.747
What is it?

26:33.250 --> 26:35.753
You said the director of
the Hearth and Home Foundation

26:35.790 --> 26:38.258
thanked Del Gruner for his six
years of serwce this evening,

26:38.290 --> 26:40.326
did you not?
Yes.

26:40.360 --> 26:42.897
Francine Bianco--
she was taken in April 2008.

26:42.930 --> 26:44.761
Her charred remains
were not found

26:44.800 --> 26:47.325
in a shallow grave
until March 2009.

26:47.370 --> 26:49.133
Right, but I thought
that was the problem.

26:49.170 --> 26:50.706
She was kept for almost a year,

26:50.740 --> 26:52.230
the other women kept
only a few weeks.

26:52.270 --> 26:54.738
What if he intended to only
keep her for a few weeks,

26:54.780 --> 26:56.930
but then her circumstances
changed?

26:56.980 --> 26:59.244
What kind of circumstances?

26:59.280 --> 27:00.816
I don't think Gruner
is interested

27:00.850 --> 27:02.317
in Tabitha Laird at all.

27:02.350 --> 27:04.887
I think he's interested
in her son.

27:18.800 --> 27:20.392
I can't do it.

27:20.430 --> 27:22.694
Oh, then you
can't come in.

27:27.370 --> 27:29.804
(sighs)

27:50.930 --> 27:53.398
*

28:11.490 --> 28:13.446
This method is the only way

28:13.490 --> 28:16.209
to bypass the chain on
a door such as this one.

28:16.260 --> 28:17.818
It is important
that you master it.

28:17.860 --> 28:19.828
Like it's important
that I study tobacco ash

28:19.860 --> 28:22.328
and can distinguish
one form of mold from another.

28:22.360 --> 28:24.123
Do you know
why most investigators fail?

28:24.170 --> 28:25.819
Lack of elastics?

28:25.870 --> 28:27.963
They refuse to extend
their base of knowledge

28:28.000 --> 28:30.468
beyond the bounds of basic
investigative procedure.

28:30.500 --> 28:32.036
Right, but we've been
doing this for weeks.

28:32.070 --> 28:34.129
When do we get
to take on an actual case?

28:34.180 --> 28:35.875
When I decide that you're ready.

28:35.910 --> 28:38.447
Do it again.

28:40.350 --> 28:42.511
You don't look well, you know.

28:42.550 --> 28:44.188
What's my appearance got
to do with anything?

28:44.220 --> 28:46.188
You've been mopey
ever since MI6 fired you.

28:46.220 --> 28:48.984
I think you're taking
your frustrations out on me.

28:49.020 --> 28:52.820
I am gifting you
with an education.

28:52.860 --> 28:54.851
Well, maybe you were just wrong
about me.

28:54.900 --> 28:56.856
Only that can't be it
because you're never wrong.

28:56.900 --> 28:59.494
Watson was much further along
at this point.

28:59.530 --> 29:03.762
Perhaps you're right
about me being wrong.

29:03.810 --> 29:04.959
I was only ever trying
to fix you,

29:05.010 --> 29:07.877
but you seem
to enjoy being broken.

29:11.280 --> 29:13.441
Don't call me again.

29:13.480 --> 29:15.311
Even

29:22.320 --> 29:23.924
Yes, Jesse is adopted.

29:23.960 --> 29:25.928
What does that have
to do with anything?

29:25.960 --> 29:29.020
Did you ever come in contact
with the biological parents?
No,

29:29.060 --> 29:31.369
he was a safe haven baby.
Someone left him at a firehouse.

29:31.400 --> 29:32.799
Why?

29:32.830 --> 29:34.195
We have_reason
to believe

29:34.240 --> 29:36.959
that Jesse's father
might be Del Gruner.

29:37.000 --> 29:39.833
What?
WATSON:
We think he abducted this woman,

29:39.870 --> 29:40.939
Francine Bianco, in 2008.

29:40.980 --> 29:42.971
We think she's

29:43.010 --> 29:45.308
_ J_esse's
biological mother.

29:45.350 --> 29:48.114
This is insane.

29:48.150 --> 29:49.811
Insane would be
a fair assessment.

29:49.850 --> 29:51.386
Mr. Gruner suffers from
what must surely be

29:51.420 --> 29:53.308
clinical narcissism.

29:53.350 --> 29:56.353
That is why, when he realized
he'd impregnated his captive,

29:56.390 --> 29:58.358
he veered from what we believe
to be his pattern.

29:58.390 --> 30:00.824
He, uh...
he'd created something,

30:00.860 --> 30:03.920
a life, and it was his, which
means it meant something to him.

30:03.970 --> 30:05.062
So he spared Ms. Bianco.

30:05.100 --> 30:07.159
At least until she came to term.

30:07.200 --> 30:08.838
That doesn't even make sense.

30:08.870 --> 30:11.862
Why would somebody do all that
just to give him up?

30:11.910 --> 30:14.970
Odds are he didn't know how to
explain suddenly having a child.
HOLMES: His appointment

30:15.010 --> 30:16.170
at the Hearth and
Home Foundation

30:16.210 --> 30:17.871
allowed him access

30:17.910 --> 30:20.879
and a means to, uh,
influence Jesse's life.

30:20.920 --> 30:23.548
He later funded a scholarship
for the same reason.

30:23.580 --> 30:25.548
I would like you to leave.

30:25.590 --> 30:27.956
WATSON:
Please. We know how
difficult this is to hear.

30:27.990 --> 30:29.958
We don't expect you
to take it on faith.

30:29.990 --> 30:32.857
We just want to swab
the inside of Jesse's cheek.

30:32.890 --> 30:35.222
If we're wrong and his DNA
does not match Francine's,

30:35.260 --> 30:36.921
we'll know
within a few hours.

30:36.960 --> 30:39.167
If we're right,
believe us,

30:39.200 --> 30:41.964
you don't want Jesse's
father walking free.

30:46.910 --> 30:49.572
There's no luggage in the house.

30:49.610 --> 30:51.874
Half his clothes are missing.

30:51.910 --> 30:54.879
Del Gruner is not out
buying Cigarettes.

30:54.920 --> 30:57.013
Well, you think he
knew we were coming?

30:57.050 --> 31:01.009
Maybe Tabitha Laird
tipped him off.

31:01.060 --> 31:04.484
He vacated abruptly
a couple of hours ago.

31:04.530 --> 31:06.282
Well, we got
a BOLO out.

31:06.330 --> 31:08.195
Would be nice to monitor
his credit card activity,

31:08.230 --> 31:09.959
but the judge who gave us
the search warrant

31:10.000 --> 31:11.297
was being generous

31:11.330 --> 31:13.969
as it is.
Generous?

31:14.000 --> 31:16.434
Yeah, we got the DNA test
that shows that Jesse Laird

31:16.470 --> 31:20.065
is Francine Bianco's son.
We got Kitty's statements.

31:20.110 --> 31:21.998
Both raise
questions.

31:22.040 --> 31:24.201
But if we want to go hard
after this guy,

31:24.250 --> 31:26.969
we need to pull a solid answer
out of this place.

31:27.010 --> 31:30.377
Well, there has to be a usable
DNA sample in here somewhere.

31:30.420 --> 31:33.082
I've already sent a hairbrush
to the M.E.'s lab for testing.

31:33.120 --> 31:34.985
If Gruner's
the father,

31:35.020 --> 31:37.079
he's cooked--
assuming we can find him.

31:37.120 --> 31:38.326
Well, there must surely
be a clue here

31:38.360 --> 31:39.987
which will help in that regard.

31:40.030 --> 31:41.554
I'll take this floor, Watson,
you take upstairs.

31:52.740 --> 31:56.107
KITTY:
How do you know
when it's ready, Del?

32:01.020 --> 32:02.248
Del?

32:04.450 --> 32:07.044
Talk to
me, Del.

32:09.020 --> 32:11.329
You_ must not like
hearing your name

32:11.360 --> 32:13.999
in the mouth of the person
who's gonna kill you.

32:16.530 --> 32:19.966
I know I didn't.

32:20.000 --> 32:21.729
That's one of the
reasons I changed it.
It wasn't just

32:21.770 --> 32:24.068
so you wouldn't find me, it was
the way that you kept using it.

32:25.470 --> 32:28.701
You're going to die tonight,
quite horribly.

32:30.710 --> 32:32.746
Then I'm gonna dissolve you
in a sink.

32:32.780 --> 32:35.544
Wait!

32:39.190 --> 32:43.456
I just want you to know...

32:43.490 --> 32:47.119
that I never stopped
seeing your face.

32:47.160 --> 32:48.525
Not after that night.

32:48.560 --> 32:51.427
The other girls,

32:51.470 --> 32:55.031
the ones who didn't escape--

32:55.070 --> 32:57.061
well, I saw you.

32:58.170 --> 33:01.606
The bitch who
broke my hand.

33:01.640 --> 33:05.007
You think you went through hell.

33:06.710 --> 33:09.019
Oh, but they suffered more

33:09.050 --> 33:10.642
because of you!

33:12.790 --> 33:14.018
(knocking at door)

33:14.060 --> 33:16.119
Help!

33:16.160 --> 33:17.184
In here! Help!

33:17.220 --> 33:18.721
(grunts)

33:34.110 --> 33:35.099
HOLMES:
It's me.

33:35.140 --> 33:37.574
And it's only me.

33:39.250 --> 33:41.639
Open the door.

33:58.370 --> 34:00.759
I was here once,
you know.

34:02.400 --> 34:04.607
Not literally here,

34:04.640 --> 34:07.131
but where you are
with him.

34:07.170 --> 34:08.671
The man you thought
killed Irene.

34:08.710 --> 34:10.598
I couldn't go through with it.

34:10.640 --> 34:13.177
You had the wrong man,
I have the right one.

34:13.210 --> 34:14.438
Does my nose
deceive me,

34:14.480 --> 34:15.572
or have you laid hands

34:15.620 --> 34:17.349
on some nutmeg concoction?

34:20.450 --> 34:23.510
How did you find me?
Your phone.

34:25.830 --> 34:28.651
So you saw that I hadn't
gone back to London.

34:28.700 --> 34:31.396
I knew you weren't going
the second you told me.

34:32.470 --> 34:34.631
If you knew that I was lying...

34:34.670 --> 34:37.491
You were right the other day.
At the morgue.

34:37.540 --> 34:39.337
When you said
I couldn't possibly know

34:39.370 --> 34:40.564
what you're feeling.

34:42.740 --> 34:45.607
I thought, perhaps,
this was what you needed.

34:45.650 --> 34:47.447
It is.

34:47.480 --> 34:49.675
I was less certain.

34:49.720 --> 34:53.486
So I returned
to the business at hand.

34:53.520 --> 34:55.659
I thought if Watson and I
could bring Gruner to justice

34:55.690 --> 34:57.817
before you acted,
you would be spared the decision

34:57.860 --> 35:00.181
that you have to make
regarding his life.

35:00.230 --> 35:02.551
If, on the other hand,

35:02.600 --> 35:04.818
we could not undo Gruner...

35:07.270 --> 35:09.761
So, why are you here now?

35:11.570 --> 35:15.131
When I returned to London
last year,

35:15.180 --> 35:17.239
I had certain expectations.

35:17.280 --> 35:21.546
Exactly none
of them were met.

35:21.580 --> 35:24.378
Our crossing paths
changed things for me.

35:26.620 --> 35:29.418
You, um...

35:29.460 --> 35:32.452
saved me.

35:34.530 --> 35:37.624
I'd like to return the favor.

35:37.660 --> 35:40.265
This is a favor.

35:40.300 --> 35:41.790
Interfering.

35:43.770 --> 35:46.432
If you decide
that killing Gruner

35:46.470 --> 35:48.904
is going
to make you feel whole again,

35:48.940 --> 35:51.500
I won't stop you.

35:53.680 --> 35:56.444
But I'd be remiss
if I didn't tell you

35:56.480 --> 35:59.449
that we had found a way
to expose him.

35:59.490 --> 36:01.515
What does that have
to do with me?

36:01.560 --> 36:03.858
With what he did to me?

36:03.890 --> 36:06.450
Nothing.

36:06.490 --> 36:08.651
Everything.

36:08.700 --> 36:11.692
Wish I could tell you.

36:15.670 --> 36:18.230
Whatever you decide,

36:18.270 --> 36:20.534
you must understand

36:20.570 --> 36:23.698
that you will always be
special to me.

36:26.450 --> 36:29.669
You will always...

36:29.720 --> 36:32.314
be my friend.

36:58.780 --> 37:02.739
Tonight's your luclq night, Del.

37:06.920 --> 37:09.559
I'm not gonna
kill you after all.

37:12.760 --> 37:16.025
Everything I've shown
you tonight was just...

37:16.060 --> 37:18.267
a mask.

37:18.300 --> 37:20.723
It isn't really me.

37:23.700 --> 37:26.260
You'd know all about
masks, wouldn't you?

37:27.570 --> 37:30.539
You've worn _one
your entire life.

37:30.580 --> 37:33.572
(inhaling)

37:33.610 --> 37:35.840
I've taken mine off.

37:40.090 --> 37:42.718
Now it's your turn.

37:59.770 --> 38:02.603
(sighs)

38:02.640 --> 38:07.339
You want to tell me where
you've been the last few hours?

38:09.750 --> 38:11.945
No.

38:13.820 --> 38:16.380
Tell me she's okay.

38:20.760 --> 38:22.955
(phone ringing)

38:25.700 --> 38:28.021
Captain.

38:28.070 --> 38:30.664
GREGSON:
We got him. Gruner.

38:30.700 --> 38:33.339
We've been trying to ping
his cell phone for hours,

38:33.370 --> 38:35.770
but suddenly it
came back on.

38:35.810 --> 38:38.404
We found him in a
warehouse on Staten Island

38:38.450 --> 38:40.509
tied to a chair.

38:40.550 --> 38:43.678
At first, we thought someone
had ﬁt his head on fire,

38:43.720 --> 38:48.953
but the doctor said it was
some kind of corrosive.

38:48.990 --> 38:52.050
Preliminary lab work
says he is Jesse Laird's

38:52.090 --> 38:55.526
biological father,
and Joan found a book stashed

38:55.560 --> 38:56.993
at his place.
There are pictures

38:57.030 --> 39:00.727
in there that he's not_
gonna be able to explain.

39:00.770 --> 39:02.658
He's gonna wake up

39:02.700 --> 39:04.907
after a few hours,
and right after I tell him

39:04.940 --> 39:07.807
he's under arrest, I'm gonna
ask him who did this to him.

39:07.840 --> 39:11.503
Maybe it's a
name I know.

39:11.550 --> 39:13.677
Maybe it isn't.

39:13.710 --> 39:16.941
Either way, I'm gonna
have to go after them.

39:19.090 --> 39:21.684
Understood.

39:24.190 --> 39:26.829
(phone ringing)

39:32.730 --> 39:35.995
There's some things I need
to wrap up with the captain.

39:41.110 --> 39:42.907
KITTY:
I wanted you to know

39:42.940 --> 39:46.478
that this is the last time
I'll be using this phone.

39:46.510 --> 39:48.774
Thought you'd want to verify

39:48.820 --> 39:52.449
that I really have gone
to the airport this time.

39:52.490 --> 39:54.856
So you have.

39:57.060 --> 39:59.927
Do you think
I did the right thing?

39:59.960 --> 40:04.966
I think you do not have
the stain of a murder upon you.

40:09.600 --> 40:13.502
You say that I saved you,
but the way that I see it...

40:13.540 --> 40:16.134
you gave me everything.

40:18.850 --> 40:21.569
Have you decided
where you're going to go?

40:21.620 --> 40:24.487
Well, somewhere I can use
what you taught me,

40:24.520 --> 40:26.886
somewhere I can help people.

40:26.920 --> 40:30.117
I might reach out to you with
a question every now and again.

40:30.160 --> 40:32.481
I hope that's okay.

40:32.530 --> 40:35.897
I am at your disposal.

40:40.730 --> 40:44.439
Do you know what I haven't said
to anyone in a really long time?

40:46.940 --> 40:49.135
I love you.

40:49.180 --> 40:51.740
(crying): _
Isn't that the saddest thing?

40:51.780 --> 40:54.772
(breath quivers, sniffles)

40:59.190 --> 41:01.784
(fire crackling)

41:05.660 --> 41:07.855
(knocking)

41:09.200 --> 41:11.794
(sniffles)

41:15.570 --> 41:17.788
(sniffles)

41:21.270 --> 41:23.875
(sniffles)

41:27.010 --> 41:30.468
Did you, uh...
you, uh, forget something?

41:32.820 --> 41:36.153
I'm sorry for
leaving last week.

41:36.190 --> 41:38.750
It was a mistake.

41:42.200 --> 41:44.691
You started something with me,

41:44.730 --> 41:47.858
and I'd like you to finish it.

41:50.200 --> 41:53.260
Come back tomorrow
at midday...

41:53.310 --> 41:56.029
and bring some goggles.

41:56.080 --> 41:58.674
And a ladder.

42:03.620 --> 42:06.680
*

42:11.990 --> 42:14.595
(sighs)
